01:18:32,484 --> 01:18:34,452
Ezekiel, chapter six.

942
01:18:34,486 --> 01:18:36,454
"Woe unto them that rise up early
in the morning,

943
01:18:36,555 --> 01:18:38,455
that they may follow strong drink."

944
01:18:38,557 --> 01:18:42,459
Isaiah, chapter five.
It's the end of the world.

945
01:18:42,494 --> 01:18:44,462
I hardly think a few birds are going

946
01:18:44,563 --> 01:18:46,463
to bring about the end of the world.

947
01:18:46,565 --> 01:18:49,796
- These weren't a few birds.
- I didn't know there were many crows...

948
01:18:49,868 --> 01:18:51,802
in Bodega Bay this time of year.

949
01:18:51,870 --> 01:18:55,397
The crow is a permanent
resident throughout its range.

950
01:18:55,474 --> 01:18:58,910
In fact, during our Christmas count,
we recorded...

951
01:18:59,011 --> 01:19:01,206
How many gulls did you count, Mrs. Bundy?

952
01:19:01,246 --> 01:19:04,409
Which gulls, Mr. Sholes?
There are several varieties.

953
01:19:04,516 --> 01:19:06,814
The ones who've been
playing devil with my fishing boats.

954
01:19:06,852 --> 01:19:09,821
- Have you had trouble with gulls?
- One of my boats did, last week.

955
01:19:09,922 --> 01:19:12,720
This young lady was hit
by a gull only Saturday.

956
01:19:12,825 --> 01:19:16,226
- Deke, I'm still waiting for
those Bloody Marys.
- Coming right up.

957
01:19:16,328 --> 01:19:18,523
Could you ask them to lower their voices,

958
01:19:18,630 --> 01:19:20,655
please? They're frightening the children.

959
01:19:20,766 --> 01:19:23,428
A whole flock of gulls
nearly capsized one of my boats.

960
01:19:23,535 --> 01:19:25,435
Practically tore the skipper's arm off.

961
01:19:25,537 --> 01:19:28,131
- You're scaring the kids. Keep it low.
- All right.

962
01:19:28,240 --> 01:19:31,038
Yeah, but he's scaring me, too.

963
01:19:31,076 --> 01:19:33,544
Are you trying to say that all these...

964
01:19:34,980 --> 01:19:36,948
Nah, that sounds impossible, Sebastian.

965
01:19:36,982 --> 01:19:39,746
Deke, look, I'm just telling you
what happened to one of my boats.

966
01:19:39,852 --> 01:19:42,548
The gulls were after your fish, Mr. Sholes.

967
01:19:42,588 --> 01:19:44,954
Really, let's be logical about this.

968
01:19:45,057 --> 01:19:47,287
What were the crows after at the school?

969
01:19:49,261 --> 01:19:51,456
What do you think they were after?
Miss, uh...

970
01:19:51,496 --> 01:19:54,294
Daniels.
I think they were after the children.

971
01:19:54,399 --> 01:19:58,665
- For what purpose?
- To kill them.

972
01:19:58,704 --> 01:20:03,004
- Why?
- I don't know why.

973
01:20:03,075 --> 01:20:06,476
I thought not. Birds have
been on this planet, Miss Daniels,

974
01:20:06,511 --> 01:20:10,277
Since archeopteryx,
140 million years ago.

975
01:20:10,315 --> 01:20:13,375
Doesn't it seem odd that
they'd wait all that time...

976
01:20:13,485 --> 01:20:16,113
to start a... a war against humanity?

977
01:20:16,221 --> 01:20:18,621
- No one called it a war.
- Scotch, light on the water.

978
01:20:18,690 --> 01:20:21,591
You and Mr. Sholes
seem to be implying as much.

979
01:20:21,627 --> 01:20:24,425
Who said anything about a war?
All I said, some gulls...

980
01:20:24,496 --> 01:20:26,430
- Want some more coffee?
- No.

981
01:20:26,498 --> 01:20:28,432
...came down on one of my boats.

982
01:20:28,500 --> 01:20:30,695
They could have been after the fish,
just like you said.

983
01:20:30,736 --> 01:20:33,534
- The Captain should have shot at them.
- Huh?

984
01:20:33,639 --> 01:20:37,097
Gulls are scavengers, anyway.
Most birds are.

985
01:20:37,209 --> 01:20:39,734
Get yourselves guns and wipe
them off the face of the Earth!

986
01:20:39,845 --> 01:20:43,838
- That would hardly be possible.
- Why not, Mrs. Bundy?

987
01:20:43,916 --> 01:20:47,317
Because there are 8,650 species...

988
01:20:47,419 --> 01:20:50,115
of birds in the world today, Mr. Carter.

989
01:20:50,222 --> 01:20:54,056
It is estimated that 5,750,000,000 birds...

990
01:20:54,126 --> 01:20:56,060
live in the United States alone.

991
01:20:56,128 --> 01:20:58,062
The five continents of the world...

992
01:20:58,130 --> 01:21:00,928
Kill them all.
Get rid of the messy animals.

993
01:21:00,966 --> 01:21:04,060
...probably contain
more than 100 billion birds.

994
01:21:04,102 --> 01:21:05,626
It's the end of the world.

995
01:21:05,671 --> 01:21:07,866
Those gulls must have been after the fish

996
01:21:07,906 --> 01:21:10,807
- Of course!
- Hurry up, children. Finish your lunch.

997
01:21:10,876 --> 01:21:13,572
Are the birds gonna eat us, Mommy?

998
01:21:13,679 --> 01:21:16,409
Hell, maybe we're all getting
a little carried away by this.

999
01:21:16,481 --> 01:21:18,176
Admittedly, a few birds did act strange,

1000
01:21:18,283 --> 01:21:19,875
but that's no reason to believe that...

1001
01:21:19,918 --> 01:21:24,082
I keep telling you, this isn't a few birds.
These are gulls, crows, swifts...

1002
01:21:24,189 --> 01:21:27,386
I have never known birds of
different species to flock together.

1003
01:21:27,492 --> 01:21:29,983
The very concept is unimaginable.

1004
01:21:30,095 --> 01:21:33,292
Why, if that happened,
we wouldn't have a chance!

1005
01:21:33,398 --> 01:21:35,628
How could we possibly hope to fight them?

1006
01:21:35,701 --> 01:21:38,795
We couldn't, you're right.
You're right, Mrs. Bundy.

1007
01:21:38,904 --> 01:21:40,735
What's the matter?
Something wrong out here?

1008
01:21:40,839 --> 01:21:42,329
We're fighting a war, Sam

1009
01:21:42,441 --> 01:21:44,705
A war? Against who?

1010
01:21:44,743 --> 01:21:46,301
Against birds!

1011
01:21:46,345 --> 01:21:48,836
I'm glad you all think this is so amusing

1012
01:21:48,914 --> 01:21:52,111
You've frightened the children half out
of their wits. If the young lady said...

1013
01:21:52,217 --> 01:21:55,152
she saw the attack at a school,
why don't you believe her?

1014
01:21:55,253 --> 01:21:58,154
- What attack? Who attacked the school?
- Birds did. Crows.

1015
01:21:58,256 --> 01:22:00,622
You're all sitting around here debating!

1016
01:22:00,726 --> 01:22:03,058
What do you want them to do next?
Crash through that window?

1017
01:22:03,095 --> 01:22:07,191
- Mommy!
- Ssh. Put on your coat.

1018
01:22:07,666 --> 01:22:10,897
Why don't you all go home,
lock your doors and windows?

1019
01:22:11,003 --> 01:22:12,868
What's the fastest way to San Francisco?

1020
01:22:12,971 --> 01:22:14,461
The freeway, ma'am

1021
01:22:14,573 --> 01:22:16,063
How do I find it?

1022
01:22:16,174 --> 01:22:18,699
I'm going out that way, lady.
You can follow me

1023
01:22:18,810 --> 01:22:22,769
- Well then, let's leave now.
- Haven't finished my drink yet.

1024
01:22:23,382 --> 01:22:25,782
I got here as fast as I could.
Where's Cathy?

1025
01:22:25,817 --> 01:22:28,718
- She's with Annie. She's all right.
- Al, why aren't you over at the school,

1026
01:22:28,820 --> 01:22:30,310
Where the attack was?

1027
01:22:30,422 --> 01:22:32,617
Because I just got back from
Dan Fawcett's place

1028
01:22:32,691 --> 01:22:35,922
- He was killed last night by birds.
- What?

1029
01:22:36,028 --> 01:22:38,019
Hold it, you don't know that for a fact.

1030
01:22:38,096 --> 01:22:39,620
What are the facts?

1031
01:22:39,698 --> 01:22:42,895
The Santa Rosa Police
think it's a felony murder

1032
01:22:42,934 --> 01:22:44,902
They think a burglar
broke in and killed him.

1033
01:22:44,936 --> 01:22:47,097
How do they explain the
dead birds all over the floor?

1034
01:22:47,205 --> 01:22:50,504
Santa Rosa Police figure they
got in after the old man was killed.

1035
01:22:50,542 --> 01:22:53,102
Were the Santa Rosa
Police at your school today?

1036
01:22:53,145 --> 01:22:56,114
- Are you coming?
- Now take it easy, lady.

1037
01:22:56,148 --> 01:22:58,708
There isn't a bird anywhere in sight!

1038
01:22:58,817 --> 01:23:02,446
"Look at the birds of the
air. They do not sow or reap.

1039
01:23:02,554 --> 01:23:06,251
Yet your Heavenly Father feeds them."

1040
01:23:06,291 --> 01:23:09,089
Something like this
happened in Santa Cruz last year.

1041
01:23:09,194 --> 01:23:11,992
The town was just covered with seagulls.

1042
01:23:12,064 --> 01:23:15,659
- Please finish your drink.
- That's right, sir. I recall it.

1043
01:23:15,700 --> 01:23:18,191
A large flock of seagulls got lost in a fog,

1044
01:23:18,270 --> 01:23:20,898
and headed into the town
where all the lights were.

1045
01:23:21,006 --> 01:23:24,271
They made some mess, too,
smashing into buildings and everything.

1046
01:23:24,309 --> 01:23:28,803
- They always make a mess.
- The point is that no one seemed
to be upset about it.

1047
01:23:28,880 --> 01:23:32,316
They were all gone next morning, just
as though nothing at all had happened.

1048
01:23:32,417 --> 01:23:35,682
- Poor things.
- I'm leaving! Are you coming?

1049
01:23:35,720 --> 01:23:37,688
All right, all right!

1050
01:23:39,825 --> 01:23:42,191
Well, hope you folks
figure this thing out!

1051
01:23:42,294 --> 01:23:45,092
It's the end of the world!

1052
01:23:45,197 --> 01:23:47,893
I better get back to the cannery.
What do I owe you, Deke?

1053
01:23:47,999 --> 01:23:48,953
- S...Sebastian, hold it a minute.
- Huh?

1054
01:23:49,810 --> 01:23:51,306
I...I don't want to be an alarmist,

1055
01:23:51,419 --> 01:23:52,915
- but...
- No one ever said you were

1056
01:23:53,027 --> 01:23:55,769
I think we're in real trouble.
I don't know how this started, or why,

1057
01:23:55,876 --> 01:23:58,149
but I know it's here and
we'd be crazy to ignore it.

1058
01:23:58,190 --> 01:24:01,103
- To ignore what? The "bird war"?
- Yes, the "bird war. "

1059
01:24:01,206 --> 01:24:03,239
The bird attack, plague...
Call it what you like,

1060
01:24:03,318 --> 01:24:05,626
they're massing out there someplace,
and they'll be back.

1061
01:24:05,731 --> 01:24:08,644
- Ridiculous.
- C...Come here.

1062
01:24:08,749 --> 01:24:10,279
Unless we do something right now,

1063
01:24:10,358 --> 01:24:12,162
unless we get Bodega Bay on the move,
they...

1064
01:24:12,269 --> 01:24:14,211
Look, Mitch.

1065
01:24:14,313 --> 01:24:17,295
Even if... Even if this is true,
even if all the birds...

1066
01:24:17,398 --> 01:24:21,215
- Don't you believe it's true?
- No, Mitch, frankly I don't.

1067
01:24:21,252 --> 01:24:24,428
- There's no reason I...
- Well, it's happening.
Isn't that a reason?

1068
01:24:24,538 --> 01:24:27,074
- I like Bodega Bay as well as
the next man...
- Fine, then help me.

1069
01:24:27,186 --> 01:24:29,459
You're an important man.
If you help, they all will.

1070
01:24:29,498 --> 01:24:31,702
Help how? What do you want to do?

1071
01:24:31,811 --> 01:24:33,787
Mrs. Bundy said
something about Santa Cruz.

1072
01:24:33,890 --> 01:24:36,700
About seagulls getting lost in a
fog and flying in towards the lights.

1073
01:24:36,738 --> 01:24:39,046
- We don't have fog this time of year!
- Make our own fog!

1074
01:24:39,119 --> 01:24:40,717
- How do you figure to do that?
- We can use smoke pots,

1075
01:24:40,829 --> 01:24:42,359
the way the Army uses them.

1076
01:24:42,471 --> 01:24:45,945
Look!

1077
01:24:45,992 --> 01:24:49,809
They're attacking again.
Melanie, you stay in here. Come on, Al!

1078
01:24:54,439 --> 01:24:56,415
Look out!

1079
01:25:25,346 --> 01:25:28,453
Look at the gas.
That man's lighting a cigar!

1080
01:25:30,139 --> 01:25:33,121
Hey, you! Watch out! Don't drop that match!

1081
01:25:33,156 --> 01:25:36,367
- Get out of there!
- Mister, run!

1082
01:26:28,734 --> 01:26:31,110
Hey!

1083
01:28:40,810 --> 01:28:44,718
Why are they doing this?

1084
01:28:44,810 --> 01:28:46,799
Why are they doing this?

1085
01:28:46,911 --> 01:28:51,107
They said when you got here,
the whole thing started!

1086
01:28:53,950 --> 01:28:57,406
Who are you? What are you?

1087
01:28:57,518 --> 01:28:59,711
Where did you come from?

1088
01:29:00,853 --> 01:29:04,048
I think you're the cause of all this.

1089
01:29:04,156 --> 01:29:06,555
I think you're evil! Evil!

1090
01:29:09,159 --> 01:29:11,148
Oh, God!

1091
01:29:15,464 --> 01:29:18,295
I think they're going!

1092
01:29:18,367 --> 01:29:20,356
We can get Cathy at Annie's now.

1093
01:29:54,191 --> 01:29:56,488
The crows again. Shh!

1094
01:30:01,395 --> 01:30:03,384
Come on.

1095
01:30:33,217 --> 01:30:37,208
- Oh, no.
- Stay here. S...Stay here.

1096
01:30:44,924 --> 01:30:48,221
Cathy! Where's Cathy?

1097
01:31:19,983 --> 01:31:22,280
Mitch, don't!

1098
01:31:50,204 --> 01:31:53,000
Oh, don't leave her there, Mitch.

1099
01:32:02,479 --> 01:32:04,844
Oh!

1100
01:32:55,615 --> 01:32:57,581
Come on.

1101
01:32:58,617 --> 01:33:01,482
Shh.

1102
01:33:28,338 --> 01:33:31,772
Wh...When we got back
from taking Michele home...

1103
01:33:34,442 --> 01:33:37,068
we...we heard the explosion and we went...

1104
01:33:37,144 --> 01:33:39,736
we went outside to see what it was.

1105
01:33:39,845 --> 01:33:44,542
All...All at once the...
the birds were everywhere!

1106
01:33:44,581 --> 01:33:47,945
All at once she pushed me inside...

1107
01:33:48,050 --> 01:33:49,948
and they covered her!

1108
01:33:50,052 --> 01:33:53,747
Annie... She pushed me inside!

1109
01:34:09,232 --> 01:34:11,198
Give me another one, darling.

1110
01:34:18,205 --> 01:34:20,103
How long have they been gathering there?

1111
01:34:20,206 --> 01:34:22,104
Oh, about 15 minutes.

1112
01:34:26,944 --> 01:34:28,910
Seems like a pattern, doesn't it?

1113
01:34:30,713 --> 01:34:34,147
They strike, then disappear,
and then start massing again.

1114
01:34:42,555 --> 01:34:45,022
Doesn't look so very different, does it?

1115
01:34:45,123 --> 01:34:47,351
A little smoke hanging over the town,
otherwise...

1116
01:34:48,759 --> 01:34:50,918
You want to try your father again?

1117
01:34:51,027 --> 01:34:53,324
No, I tried a little while ago.
The phone's dead.

1118
01:34:53,361 --> 01:34:55,919
- Still got power, haven't we?
- Yes.

1119
01:34:56,031 --> 01:34:58,930
Mitch, I'm getting something on the radio.

1120
01:34:59,033 --> 01:35:01,056
Come on.

1121
01:35:06,071 --> 01:35:09,266
I can't get any of the local stations.

1122
01:35:09,307 --> 01:35:11,296
I think this is San Francisco.

1123
01:35:11,374 --> 01:35:14,899
"...and the work of a team
of professionals. " End quote.

1124
01:35:14,977 --> 01:35:17,467
In Bodega Bay early this morning,
a large flock of crows...

1125
01:35:17,513 --> 01:35:21,003
attacked a group of children who were
leaving the school during a fire drill.

1126
01:35:21,081 --> 01:35:24,571
One little girl was seriously injured
and taken to the hospital in Santa Rosa,

1127
01:35:24,684 --> 01:35:26,912
but the majority of
children reached safety.

1128
01:35:27,018 --> 01:35:29,417
We understand there was
another attack on the town,

1129
01:35:29,486 --> 01:35:31,679
but this information is rather sketchy.

1130
01:35:31,789 --> 01:35:33,687
So far, no word has come through...

1131
01:35:33,790 --> 01:35:36,280
to show if there
have been further attacks.

1132
01:35:36,391 --> 01:35:38,881
On the national scene today,
in Washington...

1133
01:35:38,926 --> 01:35:42,485
Well, is that all?

1134
01:35:42,530 --> 01:35:45,622
I'll have to get some more water.
Mustn't let this fire go out.

1135
01:35:45,698 --> 01:35:49,995
- Did you get the windows in the attic,
Mitch?
- Yes, I got them all, dear.

1136
01:35:50,034 --> 01:35:52,296
- When do you think they'll come?
- I don't know.

1137
01:35:52,402 --> 01:35:54,835
If there are bigger birds, Mitch,
they'll get into the house.

1138
01:35:54,904 --> 01:35:57,700
- Well, it's just a chance we'll
have to take.
- Maybe we ought to leave.

1139
01:35:57,740 --> 01:35:59,706
No, not now!
Not when they're massing out there.

1140
01:35:59,808 --> 01:36:02,036
- When?
- W...We'll just see what happens.

1141
01:36:02,077 --> 01:36:03,634
Where will we go?

1142
01:36:03,677 --> 01:36:06,042
I...I don't know.
I think we're safe here for the time being

1143
01:36:06,079 --> 01:36:08,671
- Let's get the wood in now.
- What happens when you run out of wood?

1144
01:36:08,781 --> 01:36:11,441
- I don't know!
We'll break up the furniture.
- You don't know!

1145
01:36:11,482 --> 01:36:14,449
You don't know! When will you know?
When we're all dead!

1146
01:36:14,485 --> 01:36:18,044
If only your father were here...

1147
01:36:18,487 --> 01:36:22,683
I'm sorry. I'm sorry, Mitch.

1148
01:36:24,692 --> 01:36:26,851
Make yourself some coffee, won't you?

1149
01:36:30,463 --> 01:36:32,588
"In assuming the tasks of the presidency,

1150
01:36:32,664 --> 01:36:35,392
I said that few generations..."

1151
01:36:41,270 --> 01:36:44,431
- Where are they heading?
- Somewhere inland.

1152
01:36:44,472 --> 01:36:47,667
- Santa Rosa?
- Maybe.

1153
01:36:47,707 --> 01:36:49,673
Come on. Let's get the wood.

1154
01:37:27,635 --> 01:37:31,228
Mitch? Can I bring the lovebirds in here?

1155
01:37:31,337 --> 01:37:32,826
No

1156
01:37:32,937 --> 01:37:36,462
- But, Mom, they're in a cage.
- They're birds, aren't they?

1157
01:37:38,442 --> 01:37:40,932
Let's leave them in the kitchen,
huh, honey?

1158
01:38:28,810 --> 01:38:33,039
Mitch, why are they doing this, the birds?

1159
01:38:33,113 --> 01:38:37,241
- We don't know, honey.
- Why are they trying to kill people?

1160
01:38:37,350 --> 01:38:39,407
I wish I could say.

1161
01:39:53,100 --> 01:39:58,433
I...I'm sick, Melanie.

1162
01:40:00,407 --> 01:40:03,805
- I want to...
- I'll go with you.

1163
01:44:38,763 --> 01:44:40,729
They're going.

1164
01:45:52,648 --> 01:45:55,547
Mitch?

1165
01:48:54,372 --> 01:48:56,930
Oh, Mitch!

1166
01:49:14,185 --> 01:49:16,879
Melanie! Melanie!

1167
01:50:02,852 --> 01:50:06,216
Oh, poor thing! Poor thing!

1168
01:50:06,254 --> 01:50:08,551
Listen, get some water,
bandages and antiseptic. Quickly!

1169
01:50:08,622 --> 01:50:10,953
Bandages. It's terrible.

1170
01:50:15,028 --> 01:50:17,017
Cathy, get some brandy.

1171
01:50:28,269 --> 01:50:30,929
- No, no, no!
- No, no, it's all right.

1172
01:50:31,039 --> 01:50:33,028
No, it's all right,
it's all right, it's all right.

1173
01:50:33,140 --> 01:50:36,164
It's all right. It's all right. No.

1174
01:50:36,241 --> 01:50:40,232
No. Shh! Shh!

1175
01:51:04,094 --> 01:51:05,992
Cathy, get the lamp.

1176
01:51:20,705 --> 01:51:22,933
We've got to get her to a hospital.

1177
01:51:23,007 --> 01:51:25,906
- We can't, Mitch.
There's no place we can go.
- There's San Francisco.

1178
01:51:25,942 --> 01:51:28,341
- We'd never make it.
- We have to try.

1179
01:51:28,410 --> 01:51:31,502
We'll go by way of Bay Hill Road.
Then we don't have to go through town.

1180
01:51:31,613 --> 01:51:33,511
We can't stay here. She needs help!

1181
01:51:33,615 --> 01:51:38,312
I'm frightened. Terribly frightened.

1182
01:51:38,417 --> 01:51:41,509
I don't know what's outside there.

1183
01:51:41,621 --> 01:51:44,645
We better get started
before another attack comes.

1184
01:51:44,756 --> 01:51:47,814
We'll take Melanie's car.
That'll be faster than the truck.

1185
01:51:47,924 --> 01:51:50,117
- Can you finish the bandaging?
- I'll try.

1186
01:51:50,225 --> 01:51:52,123
All right.

1187
01:51:58,465 --> 01:52:02,990
Mitch? See if you can get
anything on the car radio.

1188
01:54:01,750 --> 01:54:04,308
The bird attacks have
subsided for the time being.

1189
01:54:04,417 --> 01:54:06,907
Bodega Bay seems to be the center,
though there are reports...

1190
01:54:06,952 --> 01:54:10,852
of minor attacks on
Sebastopol and a few on Santa Rosa.

1191
01:54:10,923 --> 01:54:13,413
Bodega Bay has been
cordoned off by roadblocks.

1192
01:54:13,524 --> 01:54:15,456
Most of the townspeople
have managed to get out,

1193
01:54:15,525 --> 01:54:18,424
but there are still some
isolated pockets of people.

1194
01:54:18,527 --> 01:54:21,925
No decision has been arrived at
yet as to what the next step will be,

1195
01:54:21,963 --> 01:54:25,124
but there's been some discussion as
to whether the military should go in.

1196
01:54:25,232 --> 01:54:28,927
It appears that the bird attacks come
in waves, with long intervals between.

1197
01:54:28,968 --> 01:54:32,629
The reason for this
does not seem clear as yet.

1198
01:56:22,979 --> 01:56:25,002
Did you hear anything on the radio?

1199
01:56:25,081 --> 01:56:27,604
It's-It's all right. Come on.

1200
01:57:05,975 --> 01:57:08,442
No. No!

1201
01:57:08,478 --> 01:57:10,444
Shh. Shh.

1202
01:57:37,597 --> 01:57:40,995
- Mitch?
- Shh!

1203
01:57:41,066 --> 01:57:43,089
Stay there.

1204
01:57:50,472 --> 01:57:52,803
Can I bring the lovebirds, Mitch?

1205
01:57:52,874 --> 01:57:55,102
They haven't harmed anyone.

1206
01:57:55,210 --> 01:57:57,472
A...All right. Bring them.
